        <h3 id="refrig"><a name=“refrig”><br></a></h3>
        <h3>How to refrigerate the Sour Dough Starter</h3>
          <strong>Let get us started: </strong><br>
          <p><strong>Preparation</strong><br> 
           Mix 1/2 cup of Sour Dough Starter with 1 cup of flour and 1/2 cup water together. Let the mixture stand for 2 hours at room 
           temperature. Then close your jar containing the sour dough mixture with a lid and put it the refrigerator.<br>
           <strong>Please feed sour dough weekly</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="scout-first-letter">
            Please add a note with the data and content to the sour dough starter dough so that your family doesn't throw it away.
          </p>
          <h4>How to feed refrigerated the Sour Dough Starter</h4>
          <ol>
            <dt><strong>Step 1</strong></dt><dd>Take starter out of refrigerator and let it warm up (close to room temperature ~1 hours)</dd>
            <dt><strong>Step 2</strong></dt><dd>Remove all Sour Dough Starter but 4 ounces (1/2 cup) of Sour Dough Starter</dd>
            <dt><strong>Step 3</strong></dt><dd>Feed the remaining Sour Dough Starter with 1/2 cup of flour and 1/2 cup of water</dd>
            <dt><strong>Step 4</strong></dt><dd>Note: Start feeding every 12 hours until used for baking</dd><dd>1. Remove half of the sour dough starter.</dd>
            <dd>2. Feed the other half again with 1/2 cup of flour and 1/2 cup of water.</dd> 
            <dt><strong>Step 5</strong></dt><dd>When Sour Dough Starter used for baking keep always Sour Dough Starter to re-feed, refrigerate or
              to air dry. </dd>
          </ol>    

        <h3 id="react"><a name=“react”><br></a></h3>  
        <h3>How to reactivate your refrigerated Sour Dough Starter</h3>
          <strong>Let get us started: </strong><br>
          <ol>
            <dt><strong>Step 1</strong></dt><dd>Take starter out of refrigerator and let it warm up (close to room temperature ~1 hours)</dd>
            <dt><strong>Step 2</strong></dt><dd>Remove all Sour Dough Starter but 4 ounces (1/2 cup) of Sour Dough Starter</dd>
            <dt><strong>Step 3</strong></dt><dd>Feed the remaining Sour Dough Starter with 1/2 cup of flour and 1/2 cup of water</dd>
            <dt><strong>Step 4</strong></dt><dd>Wait for at least 12 hours and keep Sour Dough at room temperature</dd>
            <dt><strong>Step 5</strong></dt><dd>Put jar back in refrigerator. Update date on jar/attched note.</dd>
          </ol>  
